When someone asks us to help them address an issue, we assume they either didn't find a "band-aid" option that worked well or they wanted get away from the band-aid approach. We assume people may want to have a start AND a stop time with a goal to graduate and move on with life. ⁠
⁠
Please don't limit the products capability or what they may do by the names on the bottles. Cleanse isn't a laxative and HELPS with diarrhea/loose stools. Its a "cleaner", not a "flusher." Reflux helps with reflux, heartburn, etc. AND constipation in the colon. Get it? ⁠
⁠
While customer service may not always explain our approach to everything well, I'm actually most concerned with them starting you in the right spot. If you message us on IG I feel like we are most effective at hitting the mark. ⁠
⁠
Here is what I am working to do to better to help you. ⁠
⁠
I'm going to begin incorporating as much information directly into the posts as possible. Then, I'll create brief, straightforward quizzes to ensure there's no confusion about the best place for you to start. This approach will minimize potential human errors in interpreting your input.⁠
⁠
Trust that the products, timelines, and doses work. Please consider entering into a protocol with Silver Fern™ like getting into the seat of a roller coaster, we plan to do a lot quickly. With a roller coaster ride you may experience lots of ups, downs, jerking motions, and different ride times. Except for allergic reactions, the answer to lots of "ups, downs, jerking, and twisting" is to slow the ride down (lower the dosing by half) for a few weeks and then go back to the faster pace as your body allows. Jumping off the ride does not help you, stick with it!⁠
⁠
We know you're looking for a "happily ever after" so you can move on with your life without your gut troubles being a constant concern. That's our goal as well.
